T1  - Exchange Rates and Cash Flows in Differentiated Product Industries: A Simulation Approach
AU  - FRIBERG, RICHARD
AU  - GANSLANDT, MATTIAS
Y1  - 2007/10/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/10/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.2007.01281.x
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 2475
EP  - 2502
VL  - 62
IS  - 5
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.2007.01281.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT How do exchange rate changes impact firms' cash flows? We extend a simulation method developed in industrial organization to answer this question. We use prices, quantities, and product characteristics for differentiated products, coupled with a discrete choice framework and an assumption of price competition, to estimate marginal costs for all producers. Using a Monte Carlo approach we generate counterfactual prices and profits for different levels of exchange rates. We illustrate the method using the market for bottled water. Our results stress that even in a relatively simple market such as this one, different brands face very different exchange rate risks.
ER  - 

